1
00:01:51,211 --> 00:01:52,610
Has it come on?

2
00:01:54,047 --> 00:01:55,173
No.

3
00:01:56,449 --> 00:01:58,110
Now?

4
00:01:58,751 --> 00:02:00,446
No.

5
00:02:01,654 --> 00:02:02,746
Now?

6
00:02:03,389 --> 00:02:05,152
No.

7
00:02:06,659 --> 00:02:07,717
Now?

8
00:02:08,761 --> 00:02:11,059
Turn the damn thing properly!

9
00:02:12,732 --> 00:02:16,099
Welcome to the wrestling area
at the Seoul Olympics.

10
00:02:16,169 --> 00:02:18,069
Looking forward to
an exciting match today.

11
00:02:18,138 --> 00:02:19,036
It's come on.

12
00:02:19,205 --> 00:02:20,399
Shall I come down?

13
00:02:20,607 --> 00:02:21,574
No.

14
00:02:21,774 --> 00:02:23,332
Stand there holding it.

15
00:02:26,779 --> 00:02:30,180
The final match this Olympics...
in the 72-kilo category,

16
00:02:30,250 --> 00:02:34,016
between wrestlers from
Russia and America.

17
00:02:35,121 --> 00:02:36,349
It's really sad that,

18
00:02:36,422 --> 00:02:39,516
despite wrestling being
such a popular sport in India

19
00:02:39,592 --> 00:02:44,052
Indian wrestlers have
disappointed in the Olympics.

20
00:02:44,430 --> 00:02:47,024
Even our boys
can bring home medals.

21
00:02:48,134 --> 00:02:50,466
But where is the support?

22
00:02:51,204 --> 00:02:53,331
Neither money,
nor facilities.

23
00:02:54,240 --> 00:02:56,800
How will our boys win a medal?

24
00:02:58,111 --> 00:03:01,171
If a medal could be won with words,

25
00:03:02,048 --> 00:03:04,608
you would have won
it a long time ago.

26
00:03:08,421 --> 00:03:10,252
Are you new here?

27
00:03:12,692 --> 00:03:14,717
That's what I thought.

28
00:03:16,996 --> 00:03:19,328
Try stepping into a
wrestling arena someday,

29
00:03:19,766 --> 00:03:22,394
you'll run for your life
before the match begins.

30
00:03:24,304 --> 00:03:26,636
Looks like you have
done it many times.

31
00:03:28,708 --> 00:03:30,232
Run for your life.

32
00:03:30,743 --> 00:03:34,042
If this were an arena,
then we'd see who would run.

33
00:03:34,747 --> 00:03:37,181
Why do we need an arena?

34
00:03:39,752 --> 00:03:42,277
Now, the moment
we were all waiting for.

35
00:03:42,522 --> 00:03:44,752
The stage is all set for a big fight.

36
00:03:45,258 --> 00:03:47,692
There's palpable excitement in the air.

37
00:03:49,195 --> 00:03:51,060
Both the wrestlers are walking,

38
00:03:51,130 --> 00:03:53,030
for the fight.

39
00:03:53,099 --> 00:03:54,726
You are absolutely right, Tom.

40
00:03:55,268 --> 00:03:58,328
Looks like it's going
to be an interesting bout.

41
00:03:59,072 --> 00:04:01,063
The crowd seems excited.

42
00:04:03,676 --> 00:04:06,543
The wrestlers come face to face.

43
00:04:07,480 --> 00:04:10,677
Let's see how it plays out.

44
00:04:11,651 --> 00:04:13,585
The customary handshake.

45
00:04:13,653 --> 00:04:16,349
The referee's whistle...
and the match begins!

46
00:04:24,364 --> 00:04:25,592
He's down!

47
00:04:26,065 --> 00:04:27,032
He's down!

48
00:04:27,400 --> 00:04:30,392
An early thrashing
for the Russian wrestler.

49
00:04:30,603 --> 00:04:34,061
Overconfidence can often
prove fatal.

50
00:04:34,674 --> 00:04:38,701
Bro, you want to try once more?

51
00:04:47,020 --> 00:04:49,648
Now, the wrestlers are gearing up
for the next round.

52
00:04:50,757 --> 00:04:56,320
Yes, Tom, this match doesn't look
as easy as it had seemed.

53
00:04:57,030 --> 00:04:58,691
Let's see what happens now.

54
00:05:00,366 --> 00:05:02,561
Both wrestlers testing each other.

55
00:05:02,635 --> 00:05:05,297
A great attack!
An equally superb defense.

56
00:05:08,174 --> 00:05:10,438
And that was a magnificent move!

57
00:05:11,377 --> 00:05:13,641
What an amazing move!

58
00:05:14,113 --> 00:05:16,138
He didn't know what hit him.

59
00:05:18,718 --> 00:05:20,242
Here's an attack.

60
00:05:21,154 --> 00:05:22,621
And that's a counter-attack!

61
00:05:24,123 --> 00:05:25,351
And it's over!

62
00:05:25,558 --> 00:05:27,048
It's all over.

63
00:05:27,660 --> 00:05:29,287
David has become Goliath,

64
00:05:29,529 --> 00:05:31,588
and Goliath has become David here.

65
00:05:31,998 --> 00:05:33,158
Well said, Tom.

66
00:05:33,232 --> 00:05:37,635
No one expected such a quick defeat
for the Russian wrestler.

67
00:05:37,704 --> 00:05:38,636
What a match!

68
00:05:39,138 --> 00:05:41,003
This is top class wrestling.

69
00:05:43,543 --> 00:05:45,135
You are good.

70
00:05:46,212 --> 00:05:48,305
You've just defeated
a state level champion.

71
00:05:49,215 --> 00:05:50,739
Don't be disheartened buddy,

72
00:05:51,784 --> 00:05:54,252
you've just lost to
a national level champion.

73
00:06:04,063 --> 00:06:05,587
Meet my uncle.

74
00:06:06,432 --> 00:06:08,059
Mahavir Singh Phogat.

75
00:06:08,634 --> 00:06:11,125
He quit wrestling many years ago,

76
00:06:11,371 --> 00:06:15,034
but wrestling hasn't
quit on him.

77
00:06:26,152 --> 00:06:28,552
# I'm here to stay. #

78
00:06:28,621 --> 00:06:31,317
# Beat the best. #

79
00:06:31,391 --> 00:06:33,985
# I'm here to stay. #

80
00:06:34,060 --> 00:06:36,528
# Beat the best. #

81
00:06:37,363 --> 00:06:42,391
# From the mother's womb to the
cemetery, your life is a wrestling bout. #

82
00:06:42,468 --> 00:06:44,993
# So, wrestle, O Wrestler! #

83
00:06:45,438 --> 00:06:47,565
# Wrestle, O Wrestler! #

84
00:06:48,174 --> 00:06:50,335
# Your glory may rise and fall, #

85
00:06:50,410 --> 00:06:53,345
# cause up in the sky
your stars are wrestling, too. #

86
00:06:53,413 --> 00:06:55,438
# So, wrestle, O Wrestler! #

87
00:06:56,349 --> 00:06:58,579
# Wrestle, O Wrestler! #

88
00:06:59,519 --> 00:07:04,115
# When your heart
thumps with fear, #

89
00:07:04,957 --> 00:07:06,151
# pat your back, #

90
00:07:06,225 --> 00:07:07,419
# bring back courage, #

91
00:07:07,493 --> 00:07:09,984
# and you'll be fine. #

92
00:07:10,263 --> 00:07:15,428
# Every challenge is
like a crazed elephant, #

93
00:07:15,501 --> 00:07:16,695
# standing in front of you, #

94
00:07:16,969 --> 00:07:18,334
# staring fierce, #

95
00:07:18,404 --> 00:07:20,099
# threatening you. #

96
00:07:20,173 --> 00:07:23,165
# So, take it head on, #

97
00:07:23,242 --> 00:07:25,733
# that's what you are born for! #

98
00:07:26,012 --> 00:07:27,343
# So, wrestle, O Wrestler! #

99
00:07:28,648 --> 00:07:30,582
# Wrestle, O Wrestler! #

100
00:07:31,217 --> 00:07:34,015
# Your glory may rise and fall, #

101
00:07:34,086 --> 00:07:36,520
# cause up in the sky
your stars are wrestling, too. #

102
00:07:36,589 --> 00:07:38,386
# So, wrestle, O Wrestler! #

103
00:07:39,425 --> 00:07:41,154
# Wrestle, O Wrestler! #

104
00:07:59,078 --> 00:08:00,602
The smaller kid will win.

105
00:08:03,082 --> 00:08:04,242
There you go!

106
00:08:04,617 --> 00:08:07,950
Merely building a good body
does not make a wrestler.

107
00:08:08,187 --> 00:08:09,279
Come here, kid.

108
00:08:10,990 --> 00:08:14,585
Wrestling runs in the blood,
you have to be born with it.

109
00:08:15,194 --> 00:08:17,219
Here. Buy yourself some milk.

110
00:08:18,130 --> 00:08:19,222
Bless you.

111
00:08:55,134 --> 00:08:59,366
When there's no food on your plate
what will you eat? Medals?

112
00:09:00,673 --> 00:09:03,073
No one gives a damn
about wrestling.

113
00:09:03,409 --> 00:09:06,640
Just take up the job
you are being offered.

114
00:09:13,286 --> 00:09:15,618
Why did you quit wrestling?

115
00:09:17,089 --> 00:09:18,989
I had no choice.

116
00:09:21,327 --> 00:09:24,228
Wrestling gave me respect, fame,

117
00:09:25,298 --> 00:09:27,357
but it couldn't give me money.

118
00:09:28,568 --> 00:09:30,058
So, I took up this job.

119
00:09:30,102 --> 00:09:33,435
Every wrestler dreams,

120
00:09:33,472 --> 00:09:35,736
of bringing honor and
glory to the country.

121
00:09:38,010 --> 00:09:40,604
But if the country offers no support,

122
00:09:40,646 --> 00:09:43,342
how far can a wrestler go?

123
00:09:56,629 --> 00:10:02,226
It's not your fault that you
couldn't win a medal for your country.

124
00:10:03,002 --> 00:10:07,029
How long will you let these
memories depress you?

125
00:10:12,278 --> 00:10:17,409
What I couldn't do,
our son will.

126
00:10:19,785 --> 00:10:22,515
He will win gold
for our country.

127
00:10:24,690 --> 00:10:27,352
Our flag will fly the highest.

128
00:10:28,461 --> 00:10:29,655
Mark my words.

129
00:10:36,135 --> 00:10:39,070
That day uncle was
as anxious as a student,

130
00:10:39,205 --> 00:10:41,469
whose high school results
were due.

131
00:10:42,074 --> 00:10:43,632
Don't worry, brother.

132
00:10:43,676 --> 00:10:44,768
It's going to be alright.

133
00:10:56,822 --> 00:10:58,380
It's a girl.

134
00:11:05,398 --> 00:11:08,094
Uncle was hoping for a boy.

135
00:11:08,634 --> 00:11:09,692
But a girl was born.

136
00:11:10,036 --> 00:11:11,025
It's okay.

137
00:11:13,105 --> 00:11:15,437
You have a sister now, Omkar.

138
00:11:16,342 --> 00:11:18,003
I was genuinely happy.

139
00:11:18,577 --> 00:11:20,772
But uncle was faking it.

140
00:11:22,682 --> 00:11:24,377
And then it all started.

141
00:11:24,750 --> 00:11:27,776
Suddenly everyone in the village
was an expert,

142
00:11:28,054 --> 00:11:32,115
in the art of conceiving a boy.

143
00:11:33,059 --> 00:11:36,119
Feed a black cow sweets made
with white sesame seeds,

144
00:11:36,162 --> 00:11:39,131
wrapped in maize flatbreads,
with your left hand, before sunrise.

145
00:11:39,165 --> 00:11:40,427
A son, for sure!

146
00:11:40,466 --> 00:11:43,799
Mahavir, here's a special prayer...
for a son.

147
00:11:44,303 --> 00:11:46,737
Recite it daily.

148
00:11:48,708 --> 00:11:50,403
Here... eat this.

149
00:11:50,743 --> 00:11:52,267
Eat this!

150
00:11:52,745 --> 00:11:54,110
Stop, will you.

151
00:11:56,582 --> 00:11:57,571
Mahavir,

152
00:11:58,084 --> 00:12:00,314
make sure you try only on a Sunday.

153
00:12:01,187 --> 00:12:04,714
On all other days,
reign in your urges.

154
00:12:06,425 --> 00:12:07,619
Got it?

155
00:12:08,994 --> 00:12:10,552
Neither did people stop
giving their advice,

156
00:12:10,596 --> 00:12:12,154
Here you go, son.

157
00:12:12,431 --> 00:12:14,456
nor did uncle and aunt
stop acting on them.

158
00:12:15,434 --> 00:12:18,733
The day of the delivery arrived
and so did half the village.

159
00:12:19,338 --> 00:12:21,101
To take credit for a son.

160
00:12:21,307 --> 00:12:23,298
Geeta, you are going to
have a brother.

161
00:12:23,409 --> 00:12:24,501
You can play with him.

162
00:12:33,519 --> 00:12:35,487
It's a girl.

163
00:12:37,056 --> 00:12:39,081
But neither did uncle get a son,

164
00:12:39,425 --> 00:12:41,484
nor the villagers, credit.

165
00:12:42,495 --> 00:12:44,554
But, in all these
"unfailing techniques",

166
00:12:44,764 --> 00:12:46,493
where did the fault lie?

167
00:12:49,068 --> 00:12:51,468
She must have fed a black buffalo
instead of a black cow.

168
00:12:51,637 --> 00:12:54,231
Else, look at my cousin
from Rohtak.

169
00:12:54,373 --> 00:12:56,238
She had three healthy boys
in three years.

170
00:12:56,308 --> 00:12:58,640
If you say the prayer in reverse,

171
00:12:58,711 --> 00:13:01,475
the results will also be reversed.

172
00:13:01,547 --> 00:13:03,742
Self control is a virtue.

173
00:13:04,183 --> 00:13:08,051
I told him to try only on Sundays.

174
00:13:08,754 --> 00:13:11,689
He must have let
the reins free every day.

175
00:13:15,227 --> 00:13:17,218
I couldn't give you a son...

176
00:13:21,734 --> 00:13:24,100
It's not your fault.

177
00:13:26,005 --> 00:13:27,336
And don't get me wrong.

178
00:13:29,408 --> 00:13:32,343
Both, Geeta and Babita
are very dear to me.

179
00:13:35,347 --> 00:13:40,444
But only a boy
can fulfil my dream.

180
00:13:56,502 --> 00:13:58,060
Years went by.

181
00:13:59,672 --> 00:14:01,401
Uncle remained adamant,

182
00:14:01,473 --> 00:14:03,134
he wanted a boy.

183
00:14:06,745 --> 00:14:09,407
But maybe God was adamant too.

184
00:14:10,015 --> 00:14:11,448
The third child was a girl,

185
00:14:13,085 --> 00:14:15,076
and so was the fourth.

186
00:14:24,296 --> 00:14:27,493
This time I too was dejected.

187
00:14:43,282 --> 00:14:46,046
Food is ready, papa.

188
00:15:01,267 --> 00:15:03,667
Turn it over or it'll burn.

189
00:15:14,747 --> 00:15:21,710
After that uncle gave up on his
desire for a son, and on his dream too.

190
00:15:24,423 --> 00:15:26,084
Hey, Mahavir Singh-ji!

191
00:15:27,326 --> 00:15:29,191
What's wrong with him?

192
00:15:32,531 --> 00:15:35,295
Are you coming to watch
the wrestling match this evening?

193
00:15:38,003 --> 00:15:40,062
No. You carry on.

194
00:15:42,574 --> 00:15:43,632
Hey, Mahavir!

195
00:15:45,711 --> 00:15:47,303
I've been blessed with a boy.

196
00:15:47,346 --> 00:15:49,075
Here... have some sweets.

197
00:16:35,661 --> 00:16:37,094
What happened?

198
00:16:37,162 --> 00:16:40,256
Look how badly
they've been thrashed.

199
00:16:40,699 --> 00:16:41,495
Say something!

200
00:16:41,533 --> 00:16:43,728
Yes, look how badly
they've been thrashed.

201
00:16:44,336 --> 00:16:45,530
They're all swollen and bruised.

202
00:16:45,604 --> 00:16:47,299
Yes, they're all swollen and bruised.

203
00:16:49,274 --> 00:16:50,673
Why did you beat them?

204
00:16:50,776 --> 00:16:52,107
I didn't, uncle.

205
00:16:52,711 --> 00:16:55,339
Geeta and Babita beat them up.

206
00:17:07,626 --> 00:17:09,617
They started it.

207
00:17:09,695 --> 00:17:12,391
He called me a loser
and Babita a witch.

208
00:17:12,631 --> 00:17:14,360
So, we gave it to them.

209
00:17:14,967 --> 00:17:18,164
They beat them so badly?
For such a trivial reason?

210
00:17:20,139 --> 00:17:23,006
Yes, shouldn't have
beaten them so badly.

211
00:17:23,642 --> 00:17:25,405
Please forgive them...
they're kids.

212
00:17:25,544 --> 00:17:30,072
We are letting go because
they are your girls.

213
00:17:31,083 --> 00:17:32,015
Move!

214
00:17:32,084 --> 00:17:33,745
Got thrashed by girls!

215
00:17:39,191 --> 00:17:40,180
Come here.

216
00:17:42,594 --> 00:17:43,424
Come here!

217
00:17:47,666 --> 00:17:50,260
We won't fight again, papa.

218
00:17:51,170 --> 00:17:54,003
First tell me, how did you
manage to do it?

219
00:17:57,576 --> 00:18:00,204
First, he called me a loser
but I remained quiet.

220
00:18:00,379 --> 00:18:02,347
But then he called Babita a witch.

221
00:18:02,514 --> 00:18:03,071
That was it.

222
00:18:03,148 --> 00:18:05,673
I grabbed him and
punched him like this.

223
00:18:07,019 --> 00:18:09,010
Then the other guy attacked.

224
00:18:09,088 --> 00:18:11,454
I caught his hair
and shoved him down,

225
00:18:11,523 --> 00:18:13,718
and dug my elbow in his back.

226
00:18:32,978 --> 00:18:36,641
They say that a twig is enough
to give hope to a drowning man.

227
00:18:37,316 --> 00:18:40,183
Here, uncle had found
not one, but two lifeguards!

228
00:18:52,331 --> 00:18:55,027
All along, I was desperate for a son,

229
00:18:55,100 --> 00:18:58,126
so he could win a gold
for the country.

230
00:19:00,472 --> 00:19:04,602
But what didn't occur to me
is that gold is gold.

231
00:19:05,344 --> 00:19:07,539
Whether a boy wins it, or a girl.

232
00:19:09,381 --> 00:19:13,283
From now on, Geeta and Babita
will do no household chores.

233
00:19:15,087 --> 00:19:18,181
Wrestling is in their blood.

234
00:19:18,991 --> 00:19:21,459
From now on they will only wrestle.

235
00:19:23,629 --> 00:19:26,097
Wrestling is for boys.

236
00:19:26,565 --> 00:19:28,499
You think our girls are
any lesser than boys?

237
00:19:28,567 --> 00:19:31,434
I've never ever seen girls wrestle.

238
00:19:34,239 --> 00:19:36,104
What will the villagers say?

239
00:19:36,708 --> 00:19:38,699
For how long will they talk?

240
00:19:41,380 --> 00:19:44,178
What if the girls break
their hands and legs?

241
00:19:45,384 --> 00:19:47,181
We'll fix them.

242
00:19:49,488 --> 00:19:51,649
Where will the money come from?

243
00:19:52,658 --> 00:19:54,387
I don't know.

244
00:19:58,163 --> 00:20:02,099
Don't ruin the girls' lives
for your passion.

245
00:20:06,572 --> 00:20:09,132
Let me try for a year.

246
00:20:10,242 --> 00:20:12,642
For this one year,
you bury your feelings.

247
00:20:15,614 --> 00:20:18,208
If I'm proven wrong,

248
00:20:18,283 --> 00:20:20,774
I'll bury my dream forever.

249
00:20:33,432 --> 00:20:35,798
Be ready at 5am tomorrow.

250
00:20:38,337 --> 00:20:40,237
Why, papa?

251
00:20:45,210 --> 00:20:47,770
I want to feed you
your favourite snack, 'gol gappas'.

252
00:20:50,749 --> 00:20:52,614
5am. Okay?

253
00:20:55,153 --> 00:20:57,087
What did you do now?

254
00:20:57,256 --> 00:20:59,724
I thought you did something.

255
00:21:04,329 --> 00:21:05,318
Eat.

256
00:21:09,201 --> 00:21:10,725
How is it?

257
00:21:11,503 --> 00:21:13,494
It's a little less spicy, papa.

258
00:21:14,139 --> 00:21:15,697
Alright, make it spicier.

259
00:21:20,279 --> 00:21:22,213
Eat as much as you want right now.

260
00:21:23,682 --> 00:21:28,244
Because from today, you will both
lead the life of a wrestler.

261
00:21:32,724 --> 00:21:36,251
And wrestlers are not allowed,

262
00:21:36,395 --> 00:21:39,125
pickled, oily and spicy food,

263
00:21:39,264 --> 00:21:42,256
in fact,
all the food that you most love.

264
00:21:46,138 --> 00:21:48,231
Consider this your last treat.

265
00:21:58,317 --> 00:22:01,013
# A messiah for the rest, #

266
00:22:01,386 --> 00:22:03,445
# a terror for your own. #

